      <!-- Resource Curse -->
      <div id="resource-curse" class="tab-content">
        <div class="section-title">The Resource Curse & Civil War</div>
        <div class="concept-grid">
          <div class="concept-card">
            <h3>Blood Diamonds</h3>
            <p>Sierra Leone's diamonds financed the rebel movement and prolonged the war.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="concept-card">
            <h3>The Resource Curse</h3>
            <p>Resource wealth often leads to corruption and conflict rather than stability.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="concept-card">
            <h3>Funding War</h3>
            <p>Diamonds gave rebels money to purchase weapons and recruit soldiers.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="concept-card">
            <h3>Global Link</h3>
            <p>International demand for diamonds connected local violence to global markets.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="warning-box">
          <h4>Understanding Resource-Driven Conflicts</h4>
          <p>Sierra Leone's civil war demonstrates how natural resource wealth can fuel rather than prevent conflict. The Revolutionary United Front (RUF) used diamond mining to finance their brutal campaign, showing how global commodity markets can inadvertently support violence in resource-rich but poorly governed states.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

